<item>
            <title>[SPARK-12941] Spark-SQL JDBC Oracle dialect fails to map string datatypes to Oracle VARCHAR datatype</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-12941</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When exporting data from Spark to Oracle, string datatypes are translated to TEXT for Oracle, this is leading to the following error&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;java.sql.SQLSyntaxErrorException: ORA-00902: invalid datatype
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;As per the following code:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/branch-1.4/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/jdbc/jdbc.scala#L144&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/branch-1.4/sql/core/src/main/scala/org/apache/spark/sql/jdbc/jdbc.scala#L144&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;See also:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/31287182/writing-to-oracle-database-using-apache-spark-1-4-0&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://stackoverflow.com/questions/31287182/writing-to-oracle-database-using-apache-spark-1-4-0&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>&lt;p&gt;Apache Spark 1.4.2.2&lt;/p&gt;</environment>
